<p>In November of 2014, it was reported by the Lincoln Motor Company that <a href="http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/lincoln-sales-surge-matthew-mcconaughey-745926">its sales were up 25 percent in October</a>, or since the infamous advertisements starring Matthew McConaughey began. McConaugheyâ€™s persona in the Lincoln advertisements is reminiscent to the character he plays on HBOâ€™s <em>True Detective â€”</em> nihilistic and detached. The director of the ads is Nicholas Winding Refn, who begot 2011â€™s <em>Drive</em>, and who was later responsible for 2013â€™s <em>Only God Forgives</em>. The legacy that Refn has started for himself, and the recent development of McConaugheyâ€™s career, are eerily compatible.Â </p>

