<p>Movement is the major theme of Lincolnâ€™s advertisement campaign. Â Any brand of car can move (we hope), so what Lincoln is selling is personal movement. In â€œIntro,â€ McConaugheyâ€™s monologue begins: â€œSometimes you gotta go back to actually go forward.â€Â  AÂ counterclockwise ellipticÂ rotation of his index finger against his thumb accompanies his philosophy.Â  This hand gesture, and the apparent symbolism of it, areÂ present throughout the advertisement campaign. Â He dismisses the notions that you should go back for sentimental purposes, or to grapple with ghosts. The latter notion canÂ also serve as a meta-joke on his role in <em>Ghosts of Girlfriends Past</em>, which represents the collection of romantic comedies that the adolescence of his career was defined by.</p>

